## 8. Posicionamento Técnico — Comunicar Superioridade sem Parecer Scam

### Framework: "Show, Don't Claim"

| ❌ Não Fazer | ✅ Fazer |
|---|---|
| "Our AI predicts winning numbers" | "3 AI engines analyze 5,500+ draws together" |
| "Random Forest with 25 trees" (jargão) | "3 AI engines that cross-check each other" |
| "#1 AI-Powered Lottery Tool" | "The only lottery tool that shows you exactly how it works" |
| "Secret proprietary algorithm" | "Open methodology. See every step of the analysis." |
| "Guaranteed results" | "15x more coverage than Quick Pick" |

### Tradução Técnica para Usuários Normais

| Termo Técnico | Tradução para o Usuário |
|---|---|
| Random Forest (25 árvores) | "3 AI engines that cross-check each other" |
| Bayesian Scoring (6 fatores) | "6-factor quality score for every play" |
| Wheeling Engine | "Mathematical coverage that maximizes your numbers" |
| Anomaly Detection | "Auto-adjusts after unusual draws" |
| Magnetic Pairs | "Number pairs that appear together 1.4x more than random chance" |
| K-Means Clustering | "Pattern recognition across thousands of draws" |
| Markov Chain | "Analyzes which numbers tend to follow which" |

### Prova Visual (não verbal)
- **Durante a geração:** Mostrar pipeline ao vivo (3 Engines Working → Analysis → Result)
- **ForensicAnalysis:** Prova pós-jogo ("You played 6x smarter than Quick Pick")
- **Comparison Table na landing page:** Quick Pick vs Hot/Cold Tools vs MegaLens
  - Quick Pick: 0 analysis, random, no coverage optimization
  - Hot/Cold: 1 factor (frequency), no AI, no structure
  - MegaLens: 8-stage pipeline, 3 AI engines, 6-factor scoring, coverage optimization

